<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I agree with Mythic's stance that the guy who reposted the comments was out of line, but I don't have a lot of respect for a company official who calls the guy a foul name, despite what he may have done.  Judge the guy on his actions, period.  Namecalling is pathetically juvenile.<P>Not only that, the Mythic employee tried to JUSTIFY his namecalling.  Not very professional at all.  I'd expect that out of an adolescent who isn't getting his way, but not from Mythic's representative.  Those guys should be above ad hominem.  It does not bode well for Mythic in my opinion.  I don't have high expectations from a company whose spokesman feels justified in using foul language and calling names.<P>Lest you think I am anti DAoC, quite the opposite is true.  I am really excited about the game and the concept, hoping it will be everything that EQ isn't.  It just looks kinda suspect to me when a company who is building a game world based on British Lore has no better command of the language.<P>Just my 2 cents.<P>P <IMG SRC="cool.gif" border="0">llux
