I think they handled every aspect just fine. I don't even mind the name calling because as a beta tester who knows how terribly hard the devs at Mythic have been working prior to E3, I understand the frustration level completely. The guy who posted the info outside the beta boards was and probably still is an @-hole.<P>Now, about the guy who originally posted the message inside the beta boards. I believe he had every right to say what he did there, that's what we beta testers are encouraged to do. Unfortunately, MANY of his statements were either outright lies or on the verge of being corrected. THAT's what beta testing is for. Correct the problems.<P>The problem is now that some of you on the outside have read some comments regarding aspects of the game you'll never see because even now Mythic is programming them out of the game. So you sit and worry over nothing.<P>But I'm digressing. Yes, Mythic did the right thing and after they blow everyone's socks off at E3 this whole thing will be forgotten.<P>--------------------<P>Nemus Imzadi <BR>Saracen Sorcerer <BR>Archon of Humility <BR>Champions of Virtue, Bedevere <BR>www.championsofvirtue.com
