<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I agree with Pollux wholeheartedly.  I too am looking for new game(s) but it is pretty sad when a representative of the company calls someone an a-hole and another representative then attempts to justify it. Their response was totally unprofessional and it does appear that a juvenile sense permeates the design team. I think the guy that "leaked" the info was an a-hole, who probably may have been a partisan for some other game, however the response from the design team was totally inappropriate. It certainly casts a pall over what some people will expect in the way of customer service.<P>Hopefully things work out in the next 5 months, a great game emerges and this is forgotten.<P>To the designers, you would be better served to present yourself as professional when dealing with the public. The guy was an <BR>a-hole that may well have intended to damage your product, however he could have made up his on accusations and posted them. It is my understanding that a respected beta tester posted his legitimate concerns about the game, so perhaps next time you should be a bit more introspective before falling prey to a juvenile "knee jerk" reaction. The original poster's comments and your reaction to this info being leaked has certainly done more damage to your game than the guy that violated your beta ToS. That guy was an a-hole but your response is a prime example of someone or (a company) that does not understand customer service, professionalism or maturity<P>IMO of course,<BR>  Eol
